headline: Why United Rentals (URI) Shares Are Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of equipment rental company United Rentals (NYSE:URI) fell 7.3% in the afternoon session after the company reported mixed third-quarter 2025 financial results, where an earnings miss overshadowed a revenue beat and slightly raised guidance.

headline: URI Q3 Deep Dive: Margin Pressures Offset Solid Revenue Growth and Demand Signals
summary: Equipment rental company United Rentals (NYSE:URI) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 5.9% year on year to $4.23 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $16.1 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $11.70 per share was 4.9% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
